  description: |
    {{API_DESCRIPTION}}
    
    ## Authentication
    
    This API supports two authentication methods:
    
    - **API Key**: For server-to-server integrations. Include in `X-API-Key` header.
    - **Bearer Token**: For user authentication. Include in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.
    
    ## Rate Limiting
    
    All endpoints are rate limited. Check response headers:
    - `X-RateLimit-Limit`: Maximum requests per window
    - `X-RateLimit-Remaining`: Requests remaining
    - `X-RateLimit-Reset`: Unix timestamp when window resets
    
    ## Pagination
    
    List endpoints use cursor-based pagination:
    - Request: `?limit=20&cursor=<cursor>`
    - Response includes `meta.next_cursor` for next page
    
    ## Errors
    
    All errors return a consistent format with `code`, `message`, and `request_id`.
    
